##Problem 2e and 2f
plot(Auto)

ggplot(data = Auto,aes( x = weight,  y= cylinders)) + geom_point()

ggplot(data = Auto,aes( x = displacement ,  y= cylinders)) + geom_point()

ggplot(data = Auto,aes( x = weight ,  y= mpg)) + geom_point()

ggplot(data = Auto,aes( x = year ,  y= mpg)) + geom_point()

ggplot(data = Auto,aes( x = origin ,  y= mpg)) + geom_point()

ggplot(data = Auto,aes( x = acceleration ,  y= mpg)) + geom_point()

Problem 2

  1. Name is qualitative. The rest of the variables are quantitative

e)From the overall plots and the mini plots we can say that weight and cylinder are well correlated. This is also true for cylinders and displacement. There is a negative correlation between weight and mpg. f) Based on some of the mpg plots above, year, orgin and acceleration might be useful in predicting mpg.
